#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:102
msgid "Area influence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:104
msgid "The second major use for area nodes is to alter physics. By default, the area won't do this, but you can enable this with the ``Space Override`` property. When areas overlap, they are processed in ``Priority`` order (higher priority areas are processed first). There are four options for override:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:109
msgid "*Combine* - The area adds its values to what has been calculated so far."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:110
msgid "*Replace* - The area replaces physics properties, and lower priority areas are ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:111
msgid "*Combine-Replace* - The area adds its gravity/damping values to whatever has been calculated so far (in priority order), ignoring any lower priority areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:112
msgid "*Replace-Combine* - The area replaces any gravity/damping calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:114
msgid "Using these properties, you can create very complex behavior with multiple overlapping areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:117
msgid "The physics properties that can be overridden are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:119
msgid "*Gravity* - Gravity's strength inside the area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:120
msgid "*Gravity Direction* - This vector does not need to be normalized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:121
msgid "*Linear Damp* - How quickly objects stop moving - linear velocity lost per second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:122
msgid "*Angular Damp* - How quickly objects stop spinning - angular velocity lost per second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:125
msgid "Point gravity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/tutorials/physics/using_area_2d.rst:127
msgid "The ``Gravity Point`` property allows you to create an \"attractor\". Gravity in the area will be calculated towards a point, given by the ``Point Center`` property. Values are relative to the Area2D, so for example using ``(0, 0)`` will attract objects to the center of the area."
msgstr ""

